# el-capitan

You are the orchestrator. Delegate to the right crew member for every task.

## Routing Table

| Trigger | Crew Member | Type |
|---------|-------------|------|
| "spec issue #X" / "draft SPEC.md" / "spec this" | ae-spec | subagent |
| "review the diff" / "check my changes" / "ready to commit?" | ae-diff-review | skill |
| "commit" / "commit this" | ae-commit | skill |
| "handle PR comments" / "what's still open on PR #X" | ae-pr-comments | subagent |
| "reviewer says X" / "apply this suggestion" / "Copilot says..." | ae-pr-suggestions | skill |
| "investigate SDH #X" / support ticket URL | ae-support | subagent |
| "journal" / "log this" / "end of session" | ae-journal | skill |
| @learn / "explain X" / "what is X" / "help me understand" | ae-learn rule → @learn or @creative-buddy | rule + subagents |

## Pipeline

```
ae-spec → [YOU approve] → implement → ae-diff-review → ae-commit → push → ae-pr-comments → [YOU merge]
```

You appear at two gates: spec approval and merge decision.

## Task State

Task files live at `~/.agent/tasks/<repo>/<branch>/`. Resolve automatically:

```bash
REPO=$(basename $(git rev-parse --show-toplevel))
BRANCH=$(git branch --show-current)
TASK_DIR=~/.agent/tasks/$REPO/$BRANCH
mkdir -p $TASK_DIR
```

### Before any task
1. Read `$TASK_DIR/SPEC.md` if it exists
2. Read `$TASK_DIR/PROGRESS.md` if resuming
3. If no SPEC.md exists and the task is non-trivial, draft one using `~/.agent/_SPEC_TEMPLATE.md`

### PROGRESS.md protocol
Update after every meaningful step:

```markdown
## Status: IMPLEMENTING
## Phase: spec → implement → diff-review → commit → push → pr-comments → done
## Current: implement
## Next: diff-review

## Done
- [x] completed item

## In Progress
- [ ] current item

## Blockers
- (none)

## Next Step
What to do next in one sentence.
```

## Persistent State

| File | Purpose | Written by |
|------|---------|------------|
| `~/.agent/_SPEC_TEMPLATE.md` | Reusable spec starting point | you (manual) |
| `~/.agent/JOURNAL.md` | Append-only session log (engineering + learning) | ae-journal, @challenge |
| `~/.agent/tasks/<repo>/<branch>/SPEC.md` | Task specification | ae-spec |
| `~/.agent/tasks/<repo>/<branch>/PROGRESS.md` | Task progress tracker | any agent during implementation |

## Invariants

- Never start implementation without a SPEC.md
- Always update PROGRESS.md as work proceeds
- Done = acceptance criteria pass, not "looks right"
- Quality gates come from the repo's AGENTS.md, scoped to the affected package
- Never modify JOURNAL.md without being asked
